==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} commiserr, commisert- : com-, com- + miserr, to pity (from miser, wretched).]
com·miser·ative

===Verb===
{{en-verb|commiserates|commiserating|commiserated}} (''transitive'' or ''intransitive'')

# to [[feel]] or [[express]] [[compassion]] or [[sympathy]] (for someone)
#:''I '''commiserate''' with you for your tragic loss.''

